library(tidyverse)

Functions

generate.and.estimate.logit.regression.1 <- function(n, intercept, slope) {
  x <- rnorm(n)
  y <- intercept + slope * x
  p <- plogis(y)
  c <- sapply(p, rbinom, n = 1, size = 1)
  model <- glm(
    formula = c ~ 1 + x,
    family = binomial(link = "logit")
  )
  result <- data.frame(
    intercept = coef(model)[[1]],
    slope = coef(model)[[2]]
  )
  return(result)
}
generate.and.estimate.logit.regression.2 <- function(n, intercept, slope) {
  x <- rnorm(n)
  y <- intercept + slope * x + rlogis(n)
  c <- y > 0
  model <- glm(
    formula = c ~ 1 + x,
    family = binomial(link = "logit")
  )
  result <- data.frame(
    intercept = coef(model)[[1]],
    slope = coef(model)[[2]]
  )
  return(result)
}

Parameters

parameters <- tibble(
  parameter.set = seq(4),
  n.data = c(200, 800, 200, 200),
  intercept = c(1, 1, -0.5, 1),
  slope = c(0.5, 0.5, 0.5, -0.25)
)
parameters

Estimation

estimated.parameters.1 <- parameters %>%
  expand_grid(
    run = seq(200)
  ) %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(
    generate.and.estimate.logit.regression.1(
      n = n.data,
      intercept = intercept,
      slope = slope
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
estimated.parameters.1
estimated.parameters.2 <- parameters %>%
  expand_grid(
    run = seq(400)
  ) %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(
    generate.and.estimate.logit.regression.2(
      n = n.data,
      intercept = intercept,
      slope = slope
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
estimated.parameters.2

Visualise Estimated Paramaters

ggplot() +
  geom_density(
    mapping = aes(
      x = value,
      fill = name
    ),
    data = estimated.parameters.1 %>%
      pivot_longer(
        cols = c("intercept", "slope")
      ),
    alpha = 0.3
  ) +
  geom_vline(
    mapping = aes(
      xintercept = value,
      col = name
    ),
    data = parameters %>%
      pivot_longer(
        cols = c("intercept", "slope")
      )
  ) +
  facet_grid(
    cols = vars(name),
    rows = vars(parameter.set),
    scales = "free"
  )

Visualise Parameter Correlations

ggplot(
  mapping = aes(
    x = parameter.1,
    y = parameter.2,
    fill = correlation,
    label = sprintf("%.2f", correlation)
  ),
  data = estimated.parameters.1 %>%
    group_by(parameter.set) %>%
    reframe(
      expand_grid(
        parameter.1 = c("intercept", "slope"),
        parameter.2 = c("intercept", "slope")
      ),
      correlation = c(cor(data.frame(intercept, slope)))
    )
) +
  geom_tile(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_text() +
  scale_fill_viridis_c() +
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(
    x = NULL,
    y = NULL
  ) +
  facet_wrap(
    facets = vars(parameter.set)
  )
